saltOS graphical installer (Calamares)

Overview
--------
The graphical installer is Calamares, the same Qt installer used by EndeavourOS,
paired with the LXQt desktop. It runs inside the live ISO and installs saltOS to
disk using the native salt package manager.

Layout
------
settings.conf                       top-level Calamares settings (module sequence)
branding/saltos/branding.desc       branding component "saltos"
branding/saltos/show.qml            installer slideshow (slideshowAPI 2)
branding/saltos/*.png               referenced brand assets (logo, banner, welcome)
modules/saltos_btrfs/               creates @ @home @var @log @snapshots, mounts them
modules/saltos_base/                installs the base system with salt --root, seeds db
modules/saltos_runit/               installs/enables the runit service tree
modules/saltos_bootloader/          installs GRUB and registers the deployment

Module order
------------
show:  welcome, locale, keyboard, partition, users, summary
exec:  partition, mount,
       saltos_btrfs, saltos_base, saltos_runit, saltos_bootloader,
       umount
show:  finished

The stock partition and mount modules create and mount the root filesystem.
saltos_btrfs then re-creates the canonical subvolume set and remounts the target
with subvol options. saltos_base installs packages into rootMountPoint and seeds
/var/lib/salt/db.sqlite. saltos_runit enables network (dhcpcd), dbus, seatd,
udevd, socklog, chronyd, and sddm; sshd is installed but left disabled.
saltos_bootloader installs GRUB for the detected architecture (x86_64-efi,
arm64-efi, or i386-pc for BIOS x86_64) and registers the current deployment so
the rollback model can boot previous roots.

Integration into the live ISO
-----------------------------
os/iso/build-iso.sh copies this directory into the live rootfs:

    branding -> /usr/share/calamares/branding/saltos
    modules  -> /usr/lib/calamares/modules
    settings.conf -> /etc/calamares/settings.conf

The live session offers an "Install saltOS" desktop launcher
(os/iso/live/Install-saltOS.desktop) that runs calamares. The signed repository
used by saltos_base is exposed to the live session at /run/salt/repo (bind-mounted
from the ISO's bundled repository, or configured to a network mirror).

Requirements in the live image
------------------------------
calamares, the salt CLI, btrfs-progs, grub (with the EFI target for the arch and,
on x86_64, i386-pc), efibootmgr, and dosfstools.
